---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Cai" noIndex={true}>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="page-title">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. Data Protection at a Glance</h2>
        <h3>General Information</h3>
        <p>
          The following information provides a simple overview of what happens to your personal data when you use Cai.
          Personal data is any data that can be used to identify you personally.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Privacy-First Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          Cai is built with privacy as a core principle. All AI processing happens locally on your machine. Your clipboard
          data and text selections never leave your computer. We do not collect, transmit, or store any of your personal
          content or clipboard data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. Data Collection on Our Website</h2>

        <h3>Privacy-Friendly Analytics</h3>
        <p>
          We use GoatCounter, a privacy-friendly web analytics tool, to understand basic website usage. GoatCounter:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Does not use cookies or track personal information</li>
          <li>Does not track users across websites</li>
          <li>Does not store IP addresses</li>
          <li>Collects only anonymous aggregate statistics (page views, referrers, browser types)</li>
          <li>Is fully GDPR compliant without requiring cookie consent</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          For more information, see <a href="https://www.goatcounter.com/help/privacy" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GoatCounter's Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h3>Server Log Files</h3>
        <p>
          The website provider automatically collects and stores information in server log files that your browser
          automatically transmits. These include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Browser type and version</li>
          <li>Operating system used</li>
          <li>Referrer URL</li>
          <li>Time of the server request</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data is not merged with other data sources and is used solely for technical operation and security purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Local Data Processing</h2>
        <p>
          When you use Cai, all text processing occurs on your device through your locally installed AI platform
          (LM Studio, Ollama, etc.). Cai does not collect, transmit, or store any of your data on our servers.
        </p>
        <p>
          However, if you configure your local AI platform to use cloud-based AI services (such as OpenAI, Anthropic Claude,
          or similar providers), your data will be transmitted to those third-party services according to their privacy policies.
          This is your choice and under your control through your AI platform's configuration.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          This website is hosted on GitHub Pages. Please refer to
          <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub's Privacy Statement</a>
          for information about their data processing practices.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to information about your stored personal data, its origin and recipients, and the purpose
          of data processing at any time free of charge. You also have the right to request the correction or deletion
          of this data. For this purpose and for further questions on the subject of data protection, you can contact
          us at any time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about data protection, please contact us at:<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@example.com" class="link">privacy@example.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 2026</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0A0A0A 0%, #111111 100%);
    padding: 10rem 0 6rem;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--gradient-start) 0%, var(--gradient-end) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #FFFFFF;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #E0E0E0;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .legal-section p {
    color: #B0B0B0;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    color: #B0B0B0;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .legal-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .link {
    color: var(--accent-light);
    text-decoration: underline;
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .link:hover {
    color: var(--accent-pink);
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: #808080;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-page {
      padding: 7rem 0 4rem;
    }

    .page-title {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .legal-section {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .legal-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .legal-section h3 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .legal-section p,
    .legal-section ul {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
